HEADWORD: Urochrome
<hw>U"ro*chrome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[1st
<ets>uro-</ets> + Gr. <?/ color.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld>
<def>A yellow urinary pigment, considered by Thudichum as the only
pigment present in normal urine. It is regarded by Maly as identical
with <xex>urobilin</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

